  "title": "Tisch der Geduld",
  "summary": "Developing a concept around the theme Tempus fugit (time flies)",
  "body": "Throught time and care a bonsai can live for more than a hundred years. The bonsai slowly grows into its perfect form and gives its caregiver a sense of accomplishment and pride. It teaches discipline and focus.\n\nThe bonsai represents balance, meditation and harmony. Which makes it a perfect symbol for the enjoyment of the passing time. However, the bonsai requires a lot of time and patience, which could be intimidating for the beginners.\n\n\n[lp=Tisch Cover 2.jpg]\n\n\n*Tisch der Geduld (table of patience)* is a beginner's kit that simplifies the care for the bonsai, making it accessible to anyone. The daily watering of the plant can be done on the table itself and the turn table facilitates the trimming of the tree. The table itself acts as a pedestal for the miniature tree.\n\n*Made in Halle, Germany*\n*2014*\n\n\n\n\n\n\n**&&Concept&&**\n\n[lp=Workstation.jpg]\n\n\nBy analyzing the workspace of a bonsai professional, we can identify the necessary components for the care of the bonsai : a low table, a turning plate, a tool box and watering equipment.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n**&&Sketches & Model&&**\n\n[lp=Sketche Bonsai.jpg]\n\n[lp=Exploded.jpg]\n\n[lp=Tisch render.jpg]\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n**&&Prototype&&**\n\n[lp=Process.jpg]\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n**&&Final Product&&**\n\n<iframe src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/127985544?color=ffffff&title=0&byline=0&portrait=0\" width=\"700\" height=\"395\" frameborder=\"0\" webkitallowfullscreen mozallowfullscreen allowfullscreen></iframe>\n\n[lp=Tisch complete.jpg]\n\n[lp=Watering Bonsai.jpg]\n\n[lp=trimming.jpg]"
}